      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> and <strong>sultanas </strong>finely</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped tomato</strong> and <strong>chopped sultanas </strong>to a pot with your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>sugar </strong>and bring to a boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook for 10-15 min, stirring frequently, or until thickened to a jam-like consistency – this is your <strong>Irish-style tomato relish</strong></p>",
