    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat, then once hot, add the<strong> pork & beef patty[ies]</strong>, press down firmly with a spatula and cook for 5 min on one side or until browned</p><p>Once browned, turn the heat down to medium-high and flip the <strong>pork & beef patty[ies]</strong>, then top with <strong>half </strong>the <strong>grated cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>and cook, covered, for 5 min further or until the cheese has melted and the patty is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>cheesy pork & beef patty</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 5? You may need to do this in batches!</p>",
